subSubSection.paragraph:
Habitat. The specimens were collected with Malaise traps at ground level in sugar cane (
Sacharum officinarum
) cultivation areas, at preserved areas of tropical rain forest at the Colombian Amazon Departament of Caquetá ; savanna vegetation, floodplain forests of the Orinoco region of Parque Nacional Natural La Macarena and areas of tropical dry forest in the Caribbean region in the Santuario de Fauna y Flora Los Colorados, Colombia .
